        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh adds bounded trusted-tool-policy projection: unreadable policy registry rows and unreadable policy bodies now fail closed, while before-tool-call diagnostics reuse the same safe projection instead of crashing on hostile policy ids\n- branch already covers agent tool-result middleware discovery, Codex app-server extension factory discovery, channel setup rows, provider discovery fallbacks beside runtime manifest catalogs, loader cache-key metadata, plugin registry alias reads, provider tool schema arrays, configured model catalog API reads, and recent mainline conflict surfaces\n- current head is `f43dc68a6738a62528b7870b8bdacbfc322dc629`\n- final focused proof ran after a clean rebase on `origin/main` at `adf981de896ace57f2e249562fbcf9580d099e87`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts --reporter=verbose -t \"trusted policy registry row is unreadable|trusted policy registration is unreadable\"`: 1 file passed, 2 tests passed\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.embedded-mode.test.ts --reporter=verbose -t \"projects trusted policy diagnostics\"`: 2 files passed, 2 tests passed\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/plugins/trusted-tool-policy.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.ts src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.embedded-mode.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/plugins/trusted-tool-policy.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.ts src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.embedded-mode.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- branch diff, PR body, and spec scrubbed for the reported plugin name and private local paths: clean\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings after the trusted-policy patch; the one accepted finding caught a fail-open unreadable-row case, which is now fixed and covered by a regression\n- previous refreshed agent tool-result middleware proof: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware.test.ts --reporter=verbose` passed 1 file, 7 tests\n- previous refreshed Codex app-server factory proof: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/codex-app-server-extension-factory.test.ts --reporter=verbose` passed 1 file, 2 tests\n- previous refreshed shard proof remains relevant for the broader stack: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/loader.runtime-registry.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/agents/schema/clean-for-gemini.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts src/plugins/channel-plugin-ids.test.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts --reporter=verbose` passed 2 Vitest shards; 3 unit-fast files / 51 tests and 4 plugin files / 195 tests\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider blacksmith-testbox --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`: blocked before remote execution because Blacksmith is not authenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, provider/runtime/channel/plugin registry projections, model/provider install catalog projections, provider discovery projection, web search install catalog projection, model picker provider catalog projection, web search setup provider projection, provider model-picker flow projection, provider setup flow projection, provider runtime hook-ref projection, channel setup selection projection, configured model catalog projection, Codex app-server extension factory discovery, agent tool-result middleware discovery, and trusted tool policy projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable env vars, unreadable install/provider metadata, unreadable catalog hooks, unreadable setup provider rows, unreadable setup choices, unreadable channel setup rows, unreadable model-picker contribution rows, unreadable configured model API rows, unreadable Codex extension factory entries, unreadable middleware runtime/handler entries, unreadable policy rows, or unreadable policy ids while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, current head `f43dc68a6738a62528b7870b8bdacbfc322dc629`, rebased onto `origin/main` at `adf981de896ace57f2e249562fbcf9580d099e87`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: rebased cleanly onto current `origin/main`, ran the focused trusted-policy and before-tool-call diagnostic Vitest commands, ran formatting, targeted linting, commit diff check, private-name scrub, autoreview, and attempted the Blacksmith-backed changed gate listed in Verification.\n\nEvidence after fix: `host-hooks.contract.test.ts` now seeds both an unreadable trusted policy registration and an unreadable trusted policy registry row while proving execution blocks deterministically instead of silently skipping policy enforcement. `agent-tools.before-tool-call.embedded-mode.test.ts` proves diagnostics survive a hostile policy id getter and still include the healthy `mockplugin` policy entry. Existing focused coverage still proves the broader stack around provider discovery, channel setup selection, plugin registry projections, provider tool schema normalization, configured model catalog projection, Codex app-server factory discovery, and middleware discovery.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed trusted policy registry entries no longer crash diagnostics or fail open by disappearing from the policy list; runtime policy execution blocks with a deterministic reason when policy enforcement data is unreadable.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate did not run because the local Blacksmith CLI is unauthenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required). AWS Crabbox broad gate was not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted local slice plus formatter/lint/diff/scrub/autoreview checks.\n",
